<br>
I also remember being around level 7 or 8 and hunting those halflings in Nektulos.  Rollo.  That stupid little..... (bleeping) halfling.  Killed me more times than I can count.  Every time I am in Nektulos, I make a special trip to see Rollo (and Travis T. as well, but don't tell Quemn!)  I charm the little guy and trot around Nektulos with him, hitting my /pet guard me hot key as often as I like.  Rollo says &quot;Guarding you master&quot;.  Ahh, music to my ears!  You have no idea!  I get a small bit of comfort doing that.  Brings tears of joy to me eyes!  (sniffles).  I remember 40-41 being hard levels for me.  It seemed I was really in an awkward level for my class.  It happens.  You can't take the game too seriously.  There is a lot of frustration to be had and some really useless BS that you deal with from time to time but in the end, it's about having fun and not letting things bother ya too much.  =)  Life is too short to spend fretting and worrying about things you can't change or about the people that try to make this game negative for you.  Ya pick your battles.  If I EVER see you in EC giving away your stuff, I will flog you!<br>
<br>
Anyway, blahblahblah!  I'm so long winded.  Jelen (fellow guildie) is gonna have to give up his title of the guild yammerer.  <br>
<br>
Allu / Steph<br>
